Hi there,

This is a final reminder =E2=80=94 on April 8th 2026, we will be removing a=
non key access to the Data API root endpoint (/rest/v1/=C2=A0) as part of a=
n ongoing effort to tighten default security across Supabase.

=C2=A0

We're reaching out because one or more of your Supabase projects have recen=
tly received requests to this endpoint using the anon key. Please review yo=
ur projects before April 8th to avoid any disruption.

=C2=A0

Normal Data API usage, i.e. querying tables via /rest/v1/your_table=C2=A0 o=
r via any Supabase client library is not affected.

=C2=A0

Your projects that may be impacted:

* urbansaudi (project-ref: caoblmehjqudocdvijrq)

Full details, including recommended remediation steps and the rollout timel=
ine, are available here:

https://github.com/orgs/supabase/discussions/42949

=C2=A0

Not sure if you're affected?

=C2=A0

You can check the logs for each project in your dashboard, a shortcut to wh=
ich is here: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/logs/edge-logs?s=3D/r=
est/v1/

=C2=A0

If none of your applications rely on the anon key to fetch the OpenAPI sche=
ma spec, you can safely disregard this message. No action is needed and you=
r projects will continue to work as normal.

=C2=A0

If you have any questions, please reach out via our support portal ( https:=
//supabase.com/dashboard/support/new ) or leave a comment on the discussion=
 linked above.

=C2=A0

Best regards,
The Supabase Team

